\par\plain {\f0\fs36\b1\i0 Cryptsetup}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0 From: https://code.google.com/p/cryptsetup/}
\par\pard\plain \sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Cryptsetup is utility used to conveniently setup disk encryption based on }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://code.google.com/p/cryptsetup/wiki/DMCrypt"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 dm-crypt}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  kernel module. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 These include plain dm-crypt volumes, LUKS volumes, loop-AES and TrueCrypt compatible format. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Project also includes veritysetup utility used to conveniently setup }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://code.google.com/p/cryptsetup/wiki/DMVerity"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 dm-verity}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  block integrity checking kernel module. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 LUKS is the standard for Linux hard disk encryption. By providing a standard on-disk-format, it does not only facilitate compatibility among distributions, but also provides secure management of multiple user passwords. In contrast to existing solution, LUKS stores all setup necessary setup information in the partition header, enabling the user to transport or migrate his data seamlessly. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 LUKS was designed according to TKS1, a template design developed in }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://code.google.com/p/cryptsetup/wiki/TKS1"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 TKS1}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  for secure key setup. LUKS closely reassembles the structure recommended in the TKS1 paper, but also adds meta data for cipher setup management and LUKS also supports for multiple keys/passphrases. 4}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Why LUKS?}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi-360\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F\tab }{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 compatiblity via standardization, }
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi-360\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F\tab }{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 secure against low entropy attacks, }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F\tab }{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 support for multiple keys, }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F\tab }{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 effective passphrase revocation, }
